# Vendored upstream rule sets are not committed by default — license terms
# vary by upstream and operators may need to make per-source decisions.
#
# `vendor-rules.sh` populates this directory and writes a manifest at
# `rules/vendor/vendor-manifest.json` recording source, commit, license, and
# SHA256 of each pulled archive.
#
# To commit a vendored set anyway, override with `git add -f rules/vendor/<source>/`
# and confirm the upstream license permits redistribution.

*
!.gitignore
!README.md
